# ==========================================================
# SentinelOps - Mount Classification Example
# ==========================================================
# Copy to: /etc/sentinelops/mounts.conf
#
# Format:
# mount_point|role|capacity_alert|inode_alert|must_be_mounted|expected_readonly|owner|reason|review_date

/|critical|yes|yes|yes|no|IT|Main operating system filesystem|never
/boot|critical|yes|yes|yes|no|IT|Boot partition|never
/boot/efi|critical|yes|no|yes|no|IT|EFI partition|never

/mnt/so-data|active|yes|yes|yes|no|IT|Active data and buffer disk|2026-08-01
/mnt/so-backup-active|active|yes|yes|yes|no|IT|Active backup destination|2026-08-01
/mnt/so-archive|archived|no|no|yes|yes|IT|Read-only archived backup disk for consultation|2026-08-01
